        "timestamp": "2019-08-08 12:23:14.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nThis addresses the issue of database initialization conflicts in SDNC cluster.  The old method was initializing the DB in the startODL script, which runs on each pod and creates a conflict (all 3 try to create the database - 2 out of 3 will fail because it already exists).  The fix solves this by moving the database initialization to a separate dbinit job, triggered by the helm 'post-install' event - so run only once per deployment.  This job mounts the SDNC controller docker image and runs the same db install script that startODL used to run.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
